  "prompt": "What is one life hack so important you know that most of the people are unaware?",
  "response": "One valuable life hack that many people are unaware of is the power of the \"two-minute rule\" for productivity. This rule, popularized by David Allen in his book \"Getting Things Done,\" suggests that if you can complete a task in two minutes or less, you should do it immediately rather than adding it to your to-do list. \n\nBy tackling small tasks right away, you can reduce clutter in your mind and your to-do list, leading to increased efficiency and a greater sense of accomplishment. This approach not only helps keep your tasks manageable but also fosters a more productive and organized mindset. Many people tend to procrastinate on small tasks because they view them as insignificant, but applying the two-minute rule can lead to significant gains in productivity over time.",
